    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "000000000000000\n1080888",
      "McDonnell Douglas DC-9\nMcDonnell Douglas has produced over 2,000 DC-9 and MD-80 and -90 series\nairliners, making these aircraft the most numerous passenger-carrying twinjets. The\nversatility of the underlying design is reflected by the diverse capabilities of the\nmodels, which can carry from 90 to 190 passengers from 1340 to 3340 miles (2150\nto 5330 km). Northwest Airlines, located in Minneapolis, Minnesota, operates over\n150 DC-9 and MD-80 and -90 airliners.\nPainting by Richard King\nPlymouth Press\n101 Panton Road\nVergennes, VT 05491\n(802) 877-2150\n© 1997 Plymouth Press\n83746 00123\n$1.95 single card price"
    ],
